alex.mojaki.boxes

Interface PowerBox<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Box<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPowerBox, AbstractUpgradedBox, CollectionBox, CommonBox, CommonUpgradedBox, DefaultPowerBox, ForwardingPowerBox, ListBox, MapBox, SetBox, View, WrapperBox

    public interface PowerBox<T>
extends Box<T>
    A Box which can dynamically change its behaviour regarding its value changing or get() being called.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      PowerBox<T> addChangeMiddleware(ChangeMiddleware... middlewares)
      Add ChangeMiddlewares to this box's family.

      Add ChangeObservers to this box's family.
      PowerBox<T> addGetMiddleware(GetMiddleware... middlewares)
      Add GetMiddlewares to this box's family.
      PowerBox<T> addGetObserver(GetObserver... observers)
      Add GetObservers to this box's family.
      T get()
      Return the result of applying the GetMiddlewares added to the box's family, in the order they were added, to the value stored by this box, then similarly notify the GetObservers.
      BoxFamily getFamily()
      Return the family that this box belongs to.
      PowerBox<T> set(T value)
      Change the value stored by this box to the result of applying the ChangeMiddlewares added to the box's family, in the order they were added, to the given parameter, then similarly notify the ChangeObservers.
